    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card describes an EI (electron ionization) library compilation pipeline, but the paper focuses on LC-HRMS (liquid chromatography high-resolution mass spectrometry) with ESI (electrospray ionization) and MS/MS spectral libraries, not EI libraries.",
        "The paper's mspcompiler is used to compile MS/MS libraries for untargeted screening of non-volatile migrants from recycled plastics, not to merge EI libraries from NIST, MoNA, RIKEN, and SWGDRUG.",
        "The research question and expected outputs reference Kovats RI (retention index), which is a GC-MS concept, but the paper uses UPLC-QTOF-MS (liquid chromatography), which does not employ Kovats RI.",
        "The paper mentions using in silico fragmentation tools (MS-FINDER, SIRIUS 4, MetFrag) for structural elucidation, not EI library compilation.",
        "The card's title mentions 'read \u2192 assign SMILES \u2192 assign RI \u2192 combine \u2192 write MSP', which describes a GC-EI library workflow, not the LC-HRMS MS/MS library workflow described in the paper."
      ],
