      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In the last decade, various open-source tools like XCMS, MZmine 2, MS-DIAL, and in silico fragmentation tools, e.g., MetFrag, MS-FINDER, and SIRIUS 4, have been developed to facilitate and improve the handling of HRMS data in the metabolomics community... they are able to leverage publicly available MS/MS libraries like MassBank, RIKEN, and GNPS libraries",
      "asbval:note": "The paper discusses use of multiple public libraries (RIKEN, GNPS mentioned explicitly; MassBank implied). The paper also describes building an in-house MS/MS library. The scope of merging heterogeneous sources is supported.",
