      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The library was then utilized for identification in MS-DIAL. The data was processed by MS-DIAL (version 4.38) with a mass tolerance of 0.01 and 0.025 Da for MS1 and MS2, respectively. Adducts in negative mode were [M-H]\u2212, [M + FA-H]\u2013, [M + Hac-H]\u2212, [2 M-H]\u2212, [2 M + FA-H]\u2212, and [2 M + Hac-H]\u2212, and those in positive mode were [M + H]+, [M + NH4]+, [M + Na]+, [M + K]+, [2 M + H]+, [2 M + NH4]+, [2 M + Na]+, and [2 M + K]+",
      "asbval:note": "MS-DIAL is confirmed as the downstream analysis tool that processes both positive and negative ionization modes.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-2c05389",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-library-polarity-separation",
