    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tandem-ms-data-reorganization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In addition, we developed a R package, mspcompiler, to clean and compile various MS/MS libraries for identification in MS-DIAL. ... we added this information to cppDB and reorganized it to be compatible with MS-FINDER",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes mspcompiler's role in compiling and reorganizing MS/MS libraries for MS-DIAL compatibility, including adding structural information (SMILES, InChIKey) to databases. However, the paper does not explicitly describe the specific workflow of relocating metadata from Comment fields into proper schema fields or separating mixed-polarity records. The paper mentions building an in-house library with 449 and 172 plastic-related chemicals in positive and negative modes respectively, suggesting polarity separation occurred, but the mechanism is not detailed.",
